commit 503b20ec4886c7d9e215516eb6634a157f9f529f
Author: Mingsheng Xu <25074053+kofyou@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu Feb 6 18:33:12 2025 -0800

    Refactor the icache stage FSM and introduce icache/uopc read ports (#120)
    
    * Refactor the icache stage FSM and introduce icache/uopc read ports
    
    This commit refactors the FSM such that the state is updated only once every cycle. It also adds new parameters to allow the icache/uopc to process more than one FT every cycle. It affects the performance mainly because:
    1. after an icache miss, there is an additional cycle of delay for the FSM to respond to the miss signal
    2. the ft fetched by the icache stage remains in the FTQ and is only popped when it is consumed
    3. new parameters are added that control the throughput of icache/uop cache; the new default parameter improves the uop cache throughput
    
    ---------
    
    Co-authored-by: Mingsheng Xu <mxu61@ucsc.edu>

